0A06E3ED.Line14.1275AB: Crane Tribe’s honor fell with Arreat, as did our place among the tribes.

31833A2B.Line12.1275AB: We carry the shame of our ancestor, Nihlathak. His cowardice stood before his pride when facing Baal beneath the mountain.

50619DC1.Line6.1275AB.Bar: Did you not hear the stories? Hmm. Not sure whether I should be further shamed, or surprised.

5061A877.Line6.1275AB.Dru: They will not aid betrayers. My kin are marked by dishonor.

E28A8DAF.Line16.1275AB: We fight alone, as we must.
